	<line/>
	<!--
	<line>For checklists, see under Help-&gt;Aircraft Checklists</line>
	-->
	<line>* Starting: </line>
	<line>  see Aircraft Checklist</line>
	<line/>
	<line>  ATTN: during start, engine throttle move automagically, don't change it</line>
	<line/>
	<line>* Takeoff: </line>
	<line>  Wait to NR Nominal (minimum at 95%)</line> 
	<line>  Push cyclic a little bit (pitch/chopper nose down)</line>
	<line>  Gently increase the collectiv (PgDown key or 'f' key)</line>
	<line>  More information on the Bell-412-Manual.pdf</line>
	<line>  Max takeoff weight: 11900 lbs</line>
	<line/>
	<line>* Lights</line>
	<line>  - Landing Lights: switch is on the collectiv ; visible from 0 to 150ft.</line>
	<line>  - Landing Lights retr/ext: switch on the collectiv, retract or extend the spotlight</line>
	<line>  - Beacon/Nav : Overhead Panel</line>
	<line/>
	<line>  Check for the last version at: https://sourceforge.net/projects/bell-412</line>
	<line>  and be kind report any bug/suggestions</line>
	<line>  Thank you and happy Flightgear.</line>
	<line>  Valery Seys / Paris - 2018</line>
